@adamnovak  FYI, this may not actually work as the temporary directory is something like `...out_tmpdir<tmpname>` (e.g. `/var/lib/toil/tmpPbBjlT/3/a/out_tmpdiraitngE/`).
Ideally, we'd want to remove the top-level `out_tmpdiraitngE` directory, but I'm not sure how we can get that as the suffix is generated by CWL. We also don't want to delete the upstream directory as it can be used by other tasks on the same worker.
My workaround so far has been to use `cwl_executor.output_dir` variable and remove those. It works, but it still leaves the temporary directory paths on the workers (I think that's fine though as they don't actually take up any space). See https://github.com/DataBiosphere/toil/commit/e149d827e9b07febf64d3bb9a2242165b25863fb for reference.

