> As well as
> 
> ```
> new ResourceOptions { Providers = { p1, p2 } }
> ```

Note that these guidelines don't preclude this from working. If the property was defined as:

```c#
public Collection<ProviderResource> Providers { get; } = new Collection<ProviderResource>();
```

You can still use collection initializers, e.g.:

```c#
new ResourceOptions { Providers = { p1, p2 } }
```

Which is compiled as:

```c#
var options = new ResourceOptions();
options.Providers.Add(p1);
options.Providers.Add(p2);
```

