I was thinking the API could look something like 

```rust
/// Fixed or variable length string and its encoding.
#[derive(Debug, PartialEq, Clone)]
pub struct SbpString<T, E = Unterminated> {
    data: T,
    encoding: PhantomData<E>,
}

impl<T, E> SbpString<T, E>
where
    T: AsRef<[u8]>,
{
    /// Creates a new SbpString with a given encoding. Does not check if the data is valid
    /// for the given encoding.
    pub fn new_unchecked(data: T) -> Self { // rename new to reflect that it doesn't check encodings
        Self {
            data,
            encoding: PhantomData,
        }
    }

    /// Returns a byte slice of this SbpString's contents.
    pub fn as_bytes(&self) -> &[u8] {
        self.data.as_ref()
    }

    /// Returns a byte vector of this SbpString's contents.
    pub fn to_vec(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
        self.data.as_ref().to_vec()
    }
}

impl<T: AsRef<[u8]>> SbpString<T, Unterminated> {
    // I think this one can be infallible
